      "writtenOn": "2021-04-08T13:25:01Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The Declaration is only necessary when we are actually declaring the variable, and I can\u0027t imagine why we\u0027d ever want two declarations for the same variable, so I think this is the right behavior.\n\nAgain, I\u0027d much prefer not having to make DSLVar copyable in the first place, but I wasn\u0027t able to come up with a way to make C++ do what I want. This is the best solution I was able to figure out, but I am certainly open to suggestions.",
      "parentUuid": "9022146d_b95930d6",
